<http://testwebsite/testProgram#Data-id_20260413053510_702-generated_answer>
    a <http://purl.dataone.org/provone/2015/01/15/ontology#Data> ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "generated_answer@en^^<xsd:string>" ;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#value> """As a 30-year-old male with diabetes and a preference for a carnivorous diet, selecting the right foods before your gym workout is crucial for maintaining steady energy levels and optimizing your exercise performance. Here are some light and energy-boosting food suggestions to consider:

1. **Lean Protein**: 
   - Grilled chicken or turkey slices can provide a good source of protein without making you feel too full.
   - Consider lean cuts of beef, such as sirloin, if you have time to prepare them.

2. **Healthy Fats**:
   - Nuts like almonds or walnuts can offer quick energy and can be eaten conveniently.
   - Avocados can be a great addition to a pre-workout meal or snack; consider making a small portion of chicken or turkey avocado salad.

3. **Lean Sandwiches or Wraps**:
   - Whole-grain wraps with turkey or chicken and a sprinkle of cheese can provide a balanced source of energy.
   - Consider using low-carb wraps if you're managing carbohydrate intake closely.

4. **Eggs**:
   - Boiled or scrambled eggs can give a quick source of protein. Preparing an egg white omelet with some vegetables can be a good choice.

5. **Greek Yogurt**:
   - Although not carnivorous, if you're open to it, plain or Greek yogurt with a handful of nuts can be easy to digest and filled with protein.

6. **Low-Carb Salad**:
   - A small salad with greens, lean meat, and a light olive oil dressing is a good pre-workout boost.

7. **Protein Shake**: 
   - Consider a protein shake made with water or unsweetened almond milk, and a scoop of quality protein powder. This is light and can be consumed easily before workouts.

It's essential to consume your pre-workout meal or snack about 30 minutes to an hour before hitting the gym, giving your body time to digest and start converting food into usable energy. Also, don't forget to stay hydrated by drinking water before and during your workout. If you are on a specific diabetes management plan, ensure you are checking your blood sugar levels and adjusting your intake accordingly.@en^^<xsd:string>""" ;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasGeneratedBy> <http://testwebsite/testProgram#id_20260413053510_114>, <http://testwebsite/testProgram#id_20260413053513_620> .

<http://testwebsite/testProgram#Data-id_20260413053510_961-user_prompt>
    a <http://purl.dataone.org/provone/2015/01/15/ontology#Data> ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "user_prompt@en^^<xsd:string>" ;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#value> "I need suggestions for light and energy-boosting foods to eat before my gym workout.@en^^<xsd:string>" .

<http://testwebsite/testProgram#Data-id_20260413053513_174-extracts>
    a <http://purl.dataone.org/provone/2015/01/15/ontology#Data> ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "extracts@en^^<xsd:string>" ;
